\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that performance data collection is systematic,
 automated where the designated work order system provides reporting or alerting capability,
 and sufficient to support the SLA adherence measurements,
 deviation analyses,
 and reports defined in this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Work Order System as System of Record
\series default
:
 The designated work order system is the authoritative source for all service level performance data.
 All Information Operations Personnel shall ensure that all triage completions,
 response actions,
 escalation events,
 and closure decisions are recorded in the work order system with timestamps accurate to the minute.
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that no performance measurement activity relies on data sources that are not traceable to the work order system or a formally designated supplementary monitoring tool approved by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data Collection Intervals
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall verify adherence status at intervals sufficient to detect risk against the applicable SLA windows established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The following minimum monitoring frequencies apply:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english

\series bold
Critical severity
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall monitor adherence continuously through system alerting where the designated work order system provides alerting capability,
 and shall verify adherence status manually no less than every thirty (30) minutes from triage completion until the response action is logged.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english

\series bold
Urgent severity
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall verify adherence status manually no less than every one (1) business hour from triage completion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english

\series bold
High severity
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall verify adherence status no less than every four (4) business hours from triage completion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english

\series bold
Normal and Low severity
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall review adherence in aggregate no less than weekly.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
These intervals represent minimum monitoring frequency.
 Where the designated work order system provides continuous automated alerting,
 the Assistant IT Director shall configure and maintain it to supplement the manual review obligations defined above.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Required Data Elements
\series default
:
 For each closed work order,
 the assigned technician shall capture and retain the following elements to support SLA adherence measurement:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Work order identifier and submission timestamp.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Assigned severity level at triage completion and triage completion timestamp.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Response action timestamp and responding technician.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Resolution or escalation timestamp and disposition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Any reclassifications with documented rationale.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Asset support classification (IT-Managed,
 IT-Supported,
 or Vendor-Managed) as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (IT Asset Management Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Escalation chain and vendor contact timestamps where applicable.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automated Monitoring Tools
\series default
:
 Where automated monitoring tools are deployed to support service delivery,
 the Assistant IT Director shall ensure that tool outputs are integrated with the work order system or formally reconciled against it at minimum weekly.
 The Assistant IT Director shall review tool configurations and data collection parameters no less than annually and shall submit proposed changes to the IT Director for approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 SLA Adherence Monitoring
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall maintain ongoing visibility into SLA adherence across all active work orders,
 using the performance data defined in Section 6.1 and the service level commitments established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Adherence Tracking
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a current adherence view of all open work orders that are within or approaching their response or resolution windows.
 The Assistant IT Director shall update this view continuously from the work order system and shall make it accessible to Information Operations Personnel for self-monitoring.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
At-Risk Identification
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall classify a work order as At-Risk when seventy-five percent (75%) or more of its applicable response or resolution window has elapsed without the required action being completed.
 At the time of At-Risk classification,
 the Assistant IT Director shall notify the assigned technician and flag the work order status in the system.
 The assigned technician shall acknowledge the At-Risk flag and provide a written status update within one (1) business hour of notification.
 If the assigned technician does not acknowledge the At-Risk flag within the one (1) business hour window,
 the Assistant IT Director shall escalate the work order directly and document the escalation in the work order record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Breach Detection
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall record a work order as an SLA Breach when the applicable response or resolution commitment has not been met by the deadline established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Assistant IT Director shall record all SLA Breaches in the work order system with a Breach designation,
 the breach timestamp,
 and the technician of record at time of breach.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 SLA Breaches are distinct from formal escalations.
 A work order may breach a commitment and remain under active remediation.
\end_layout

\end_deeper

