\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Recurring Ticket Analysis and Upward Reporting Integration
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Recurring Ticket Identification
\series default
:
 As defined in this section,
 a work order shall be flagged as a Recurring Ticket when the same user submits a work order in the same work order category as a prior closed work order within any rolling ninety (90) calendar day window,
 and the prior work order was closed as resolved.
 The Assistant IT Director shall review the work order system monthly to identify Recurring Ticket patterns and shall ensure that all Recurring Tickets are flagged in the system.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 The Recurring Ticket construct defined in this section is distinct from the Recurring Incident Trigger defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Operational Incident Management Policy),
 Section 6.6.
 The Recurring Ticket identifies user-centric recurrence patterns within a ninety (90) calendar day window for reporting purposes.
 The Recurring Incident Trigger identifies asset-centric failure patterns within a thirty (30) calendar day window for Problem investigation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Both constructs may identify the same work orders;
 they serve different governance functions and both shall be evaluated independently.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Root Cause Assignment
\series default
:
 Each Recurring Ticket flag shall trigger assignment of a root cause determination by the Assistant IT Director or delegated technician.
 The Assistant IT Director or delegated technician shall document root cause determinations in the work order record within five (5) business days of the Recurring Ticket flag and shall classify the cause as one of the following:
 (a) user training or documentation gap,
 (b) unresolved underlying technical issue,
 (c) process failure,
 or (d) environmental or infrastructure condition.
 The Assistant IT Director shall report root cause classifications in the Monthly Performance Summary Report.
\end_layout

